✅ 1️⃣ volatile Keyword
🔹 Definition:

volatile is a keyword in Java that ensures a variable’s value is always read from and written to main memory, not from a thread’s local cache.

🔹 What problem it solves?

It solves the visibility problem between threads.

🔹 Important Points:

Ensures visibility

Does NOT ensure atomicity

Used for flags (like stop signals)

✅ 2️⃣ Atomic (Atomic Classes)
🔹 Definition:

Atomic classes provide thread-safe operations on single variables without using synchronization.

They perform operations as a single, indivisible unit.

✅ 3️⃣ synchronized Keyword
🔹 Definition:

synchronized is a keyword that allows only one thread at a time to access a block of code or method.

It provides mutual exclusion (locking).

✅ 4️⃣ Race Condition
🔹 Definition:

A race condition occurs when multiple threads access and modify shared data at the same time, causing inconsistent or incorrect results.


